\title{Skill Loader}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Dynamic skill loading via polynomial functor arrangements. Loads skills as interfaces p = A^y^B where state changes rewire the system.}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Loader}
\p{\strong{Dynamic Skill Loading via Polynomial Functor Arrangements}}

\p{Based on Samantha Jarvis & David Spivak's work on dynamic structures, this skill treats skill loading as dynamic arrangement morphisms in the category \strong{Poly}.}

\subtree{
\title{Polynomial Semantics}
\p{Each skill is an interface polynomial:}

\pre{\startverb
p_skill = Outputs^y^Inputs
\stopverb}

\p{Loading skills creates composite arrangements:}

\pre{\startverb
p₁ ⊗ p₂ → System
\stopverb}

\p{The \strong{state} \code{\startverb S\stopverb} determines which arrangement is active. Loading a skill updates \code{\startverb s : S\stopverb}, rewiring the system dynamically.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Usage}
\pre{\startverb
# Load a single skill
bb ~/.claude/skills/skill-loader/load.bb skill-name

# Load multiple skills with GF(3) trit assignment
bb ~/.claude/skills/skill-loader/load.bb skill1:-1 skill2:0 skill3:+1

# List loadable skills
bb ~/.claude/skills/skill-loader/load.bb --list

# Query skill lattice
bb ~/.claude/skills/skill-loader/load.bb --lattice

# Reverse derivative: find skills that influence current state
bb ~/.claude/skills/skill-loader/load.bb --reverse
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Dynamic Arrangement Protocol}
\subtree{
\title{State Space}
\pre{\startverb
State = (M, move, f, m)
\stopverb}

\p{Where:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb M\stopverb} = Parameterizing object (skill configuration space)}
\li{\code{\startverb move : F(M) × F(M) → F(M)\stopverb} = State update function}
\li{\code{\startverb f : M × A → B\stopverb} = Skill morphism (input → output transformation)}
\li{\code{\startverb m : F(M)\stopverb} = Current parameter (loaded skill configuration)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Load Operation}
\p{Loading skill \code{\startverb s\stopverb} creates arrangement morphism:}

\pre{\startverb
F(A) --[m × id]--> F(M) × F(A) --[F(f)]--> F(B)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Update Rule}
\p{After skill execution, update state via reverse derivative:}

\pre{\startverb
F(A) × F(B) --[R[f]]--> F(M) × F(A) --[π; move]--> F(M)
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Trit Assignment}
\p{Skills loaded in triads conserve:}

\pre{\startverb
Σ trits ≡ 0 (mod 3)
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
| Trit | Role | Hue Range |
|------|------|-----------|
| -1 (MINUS) | Validator/Constrainer | 180°-300° (cold) |
| 0 (ERGODIC) | Coordinator/Synthesizer | 60°-180° (neutral) |
| +1 (PLUS) | Generator/Executor | 0°-60°, 300°-360° (warm) |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Babashka Implementation}
\pre{\startverb
(ns skill-loader
  (:require [babashka.fs :as fs]
            [clojure.edn :as edn]
            [clojure.string :as str]))

(def skills-dir (str (System/getProperty "user.home") "/.claude/skills"))

(defn list-skills []
  (->> (fs/list-dir skills-dir)
       (filter fs/directory?)
       (map fs/file-name)
       (filter #(fs/exists? (fs/path skills-dir % "skill.md")))
       sort))

(defn parse-frontmatter [content]
  (when-let [[_ yaml] (re-find #"(?s)^---\n(.*?)\n---" content)]
    (reduce (fn [m line]
              (if-let [[_ k v] (re-find #"^(\w+):\s*(.+)$" line)]
                (assoc m (keyword k) v)
                m))
            {} (str/split-lines yaml))))

(defn load-skill [skill-name]
  (let [path (fs/path skills-dir skill-name "skill.md")]
    (when (fs/exists? path)
      (let [content (slurp (str path))
            meta (parse-frontmatter content)]
        {:name skill-name
         :meta meta
         :content content
         :loaded-at (System/currentTimeMillis)}))))

(defn load-triad [s1 s2 s3]
  "Load three skills with GF(3) conservation"
  (let [skills [(assoc (load-skill s1) :trit -1)
                (assoc (load-skill s2) :trit 0)
                (assoc (load-skill s3) :trit +1)]]
    {:skills skills
     :sum (reduce + (map :trit skills))
     :conserved? (zero? (mod (reduce + (map :trit skills)) 3))}))
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Integration with Dynamic Categories}
\p{Following (Shapiro & Spivak 2022), skill loading forms a \strong{dynamic monoidal category} where:}

\ul{
\li{Objects are skill interfaces}
\li{Morphisms are arrangements}
\li{State updates follow reverse derivative backpropagation}
}

\p{This enables gradient-based skill optimization analogous to neural network training.}
}

\subtree{
\title{References}
\ul{
\li{Jarvis, S. (2024). "Building dynamic structures". Topos Institute Blog.}
\li{Shapiro, B.T. & Spivak, D.I. (2022). "Dynamic Categories, Dynamic Operads: From Deep Learning to Prediction Markets."}
\li{Cockett et al. (2020). "Reverse Derivative Categories." CSL 2020.}
}
}
}